%% Architecture of "the Lab" — Context-Aware Multi-Agent Orchestration via MCP
%% Render: https://mermaid.live  or  `mmdc -i architecture.mmd -o architecture.png`
%% Key figure for memoria §3 (Análisis y diseño). Keep in sync with TFG_Workbook.md §2.
flowchart TB
    goal([ML goal]) --> LAB

    subgraph LAB["THE LAB · orchestrator core (hand-rolled)"]
        CTX["Context store /<br/>experiment log (SQLite)"]
        RAG["RAG retrieval (CORE)<br/>within-run docs + cross-run memory"]
        REG["Agent + module registry"]
        CLI["MCP client / router"]
    end

    subgraph AGENTS["Specialized agents"]
        DA["Data agent"]
        TR["Trainer agent"]
        EV["Evaluator agent"]
        DE["Deployer agent"]
    end

    subgraph MODS["MCP modules (FastMCP servers)"]
        M1["capability tools<br/>(one capability per module)"]
    end

    LAB -->|routes sub-goals| AGENTS
    AGENTS -->|each capability =<br/>an MCP tool call| MODS
    AGENTS -.->|read/write runs| CTX
    CTX -->|indexed by| RAG
    AGENTS -->|retrieve: within-run + cross-run| RAG
    DE -->|serves model| ENDPOINT["Live FastAPI endpoint<br/>(put-to-life)"]

    subgraph OPEN["Layer 2 · openness"]
        BUILD["Builder agent (OpenCode)<br/>scaffold → sandbox → HUMAN APPROVAL"]
        CONN["Documented connection interface<br/>+ template + CONTRIBUTING"]
    end

    gap{{capability gap}} --> BUILD
    BUILD -->|registers new module| MODS
    CONN -->|3rd parties add modules| MODS

    subgraph L3["Layer 3 · optional, late (SEPARATE from RAG — no GraphRAG)"]
        GRAPH["Graph memory (independent)"]
    end
    CTX -.->|optional| GRAPH

    classDef opt fill:#eee,stroke:#999,stroke-dasharray:4 3;
    class L3,GRAPH opt;
